{"title_page": "Stig Gustafsson", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| embed = \n| name = Stig Gustafsson\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1930|5|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = \n| clubs1 = [[Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll|Djurg\u00e5rdens IF]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| totalcaps = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n\n'''Stig Gustafsson''' (born 5 May 1930) is a Swedish former [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[defender (association football)|defender]].<ref>{{Worldfootball.net|stig-gustafsson}}</ref> He made 112 [[Allsvenskan]] appearances for [[Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll|Djurg\u00e5rdens IF]].<ref>{{cite book |editor-last=Persson |editor-first=Gunnar |title=Allsvenskan genom tiderna |publisher=Str\u00f6mbergs/Brunnhages |year=1988 |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Djurg\u00e5rdens IF'''\n* [[Allsvenskan]]:<ref>http://www.difarkivet.se/dif_sm_guld_seniorer.pdf</ref> 1959\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gustafsson, Stig}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Allsvenskan players]]\n[[Category:Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| embed = \n| name = Stig Gustafsson\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1930|5|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| position = \n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = \n| clubs1 = [[Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll|Djurg\u00e5rdens IF]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| totalcaps = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n\n'''Stig Gustafsson''' (born 5 May 1930)<ref>http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/stig-gustafsson/</ref> is a former Swedish footballer. He made 112 [[Allsvenskan]] appearances for [[Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll|Djurg\u00e5rdens IF]].<ref>{{cite book |editor-last=Persson |editor-first=Gunnar |title=Allsvenskan genom tiderna |publisher=Str\u00f6mbergs/Brunnhages |year=1988 |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n\n=== Club ===\n\n; [[Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll|Djurg\u00e5rdens IF]]:\n* [[Allsvenskan]]:<ref>http://www.difarkivet.se/dif_sm_guld_seniorer.pdf</ref> 1959\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gustafsson, Stig}}\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Allsvenskan players]]\n[[Category:Djurg\u00e5rdens IF Fotboll players]]\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association footballers not categorized by position]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix playing position category.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stig_Gustafsson"}
{"title_page": "1998 Stinkers Bad Movie Awards", "text_new": "{{short description|Award ceremony presented by the Stinkers Bad Movie Awards in 2006}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 21\n| award            = Stinkers Bad Movie Awards\n| date             = 1999\n| film             =''[[Spice World (film)|Spice World]]''\n| most_wins        =''[[Spice World (film)|Spice World]]'', ''[[Armageddon (1998 film)|Armageddon]]'', ''[[The Avengers (1998 film)|The Avengers]]'', and ''[[Godzilla (1998 film)|Godzilla]]'' (2)\n| most_nominations =''[[The Avengers (1998 film)|The Avengers]]'' (8)\n| last             = 1997\n| next             = 1999\n}}\n\nThe '''21st [[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards]]''' were released by the Hastings Bad Cinema Society in 1999 to honour the worst films the film industry had to offer in 1998.\n\nAccording to founders Ray Wright and Mike Lancaster, they were quite surprised by how ''The Avengers'' lost to ''Spice World'' in the run for Worst Picture. They also stated that while pressured to include ''Armageddon'' and ''Godzilla'' on the Worst Picture ballot, they ultimately felt that ''Blues Brothers 2000'' was more deserving. They then admitted that if they expanded the Worst Picture category to ten films, they would have added ''Armaggeddon'', ''Babe: Pig in the City'', ''Godzilla'', ''Krippendorf's Tribe'', and ''Meet the Deedles'' to the ballot. Lancaster put ''Lost in Space'' as the one 1998 film among his five worst movies of the 1990s, alongside ''[[It's Pat]]'', ''[[Kids (film)|Kids]]'', ''[[Nothing but Trouble (1991 film)|Nothing but Trouble]]'', and ''[[Ready to Wear]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Q & A with the Stinkers |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010413025218/http://thestinkers.com/qanda.html |website=The Stinkers |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nListed as follows are the different categories with their respective winners and nominees, including Worst Picture and its dishonourable mentions, which are films that were considered for Worst Picture but ultimately failed to make the final ballot (37 total). All winners are highlighted.\n\n== Winners and Nominees ==\n\n=== Worst Picture ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Film<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070103155058/http://theenvelope.latimes.com/extras/lostmind/year/1998/1998st.htm|title=Past Winners Database|date=January 3, 2007|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Production company(s)\n! Percentage of Votes\n|- style=\"background:#FAEB86\"\n| '''''[[Spice World (film)|Spice World]]'''''\n| '''[[Columbia Pictures|Sony]]'''\n| '''44%'''\n|-\n| ''[[An Alan Smithee Film: Burn Hollywood Burn]]''\n| [[Hollywood Pictures]]\n| 9%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[The Avengers (1998 film)|The Avengers]]''\n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| 25%\n|-\n| ''[[Blues Brothers 2000]]''\n| [[Universal Pictures]]\n| 10%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[Lost in Space (film)|Lost in Space]]''\n| [[New Line Cinema]]\n| 12%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Dishonourable Mentions ====\n{{div col|colwidth=32em}}\n* ''[[Air Bud: Golden Receiver]]'' ([[Dimension Films|Dimension]])\n* ''[[Armageddon (1998 film)|Armageddon]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Babe: Pig in the City]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Barney's Great Adventure]]'' ([[PolyGram Filmed Entertainment|PolyGram]])\n* ''[[BASEketball]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Blade (film)|Blade]]'' ([[New Line Cinema|New Line]])\n* ''[[Chairman of the Board (film)|Chairman of the Board]]'' ([[Trimark Pictures|Trimark]])\n* ''[[Deep Impact (film)|Deep Impact]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas (film)|Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[54 (film)|54]]'' ([[Miramax Films|Miramax]])\n* ''[[Godzilla (1998 film)|Godzilla]]'' (aka \"Godawful\") ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Great Expectations (1998 film)|Great Expectations]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[He Got Game]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Hope Floats]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[Hush (1998 film)|Hush]]'' ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[I Still Know What You Did Last Summer]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Kissing a Fool]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Krippendorf's Tribe]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Lethal Weapon 4]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Major League: Back to the Minors]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[The Man in the Iron Mask (1998 film)|The Man in the Iron Mask]]'' ([[United Artists]])\n* ''[[Meet Joe Black]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Meet the Deedles]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n* ''[[The Odd Couple II]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Patch Adams (film)|Patch Adams]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Psycho (1998 film)|Psycho]]'' (the shot-for-shot remake) ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[The Replacement Killers]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Six Days, Seven Nights]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Slappy and the Stinkers]]'' ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Species II]]'' ([[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer|MGM]])\n* ''[[Sphere (1998 film)|Sphere]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Tarzan and the Lost City]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[3 Ninjas: High Noon at Mega Mountain]]'' ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[U.S. Marshals (film)|U.S. Marshals]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* [[Vampires (1998 film)|John Carpenter's ''Vampires'']] ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[The Waterboy]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Wrongfully Accused]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Other Categories ===\n\n==== Worst Director ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Jeremiah Chechik]] for ''[[The Avengers (1998 film)|The Avengers]]'''